76561198112536267,Recommended,504370,25677877,"Posted: 24 September, 2016",all,Cloudwalker,"Just adding my Recommendation to the already overwhelmingly positive rating. I've played a lot of MOBA's out there, and this game eliminates everything I have ever thought frustrating about them. Instead of farming and item building and ganking and getting raged at, this game comes down to two things: You, and your ability to open a can of whoop♥♥♥♥♥THE COMMUNITYAs of now, this game also has an incredible community. Sure I've gotten literally 3 (I've been counting) ragers so far, but in almost 30 hours of play at 6-15min game times? That's pretty incredible. For the most part ""gg, wp, my bad, Hey duders let's try this strat, and NICE ONE MAN!"" are the only things you're going to see in chat, so if the toxic communities of MOBA's deters you, please do not hesitate to check this out. If I had to venture a guess as to why most people aren't jerks here it's probably a few things.1.) It's new. Simple.2.) It's pretty darn easy to see how you just got outplayed and lost and as long as you're trying to improve you'll notice.3.) It's entirely possible to 1v2 or even 1v3 if you've got dem mad skillzTHE GAMEPLAYDon't let the naysayers fool you, this game is very balanced. You DO have to change strats depending upon whom it is you're facing. I've had moments where I was like ""what the heck, Pearl can outheal 2 dps? Cooomon."" But then you take a look at the Battlerites you pick prior to the games startup. Do you need some extra damage? There's a battlerite for that to combat the boosted heal battlerite they just picked. Do you need some extra mobility to keep yourself alive while being hunted by their dps and tank? There's a battlerite for that. Do you need some extra Utility for the tossup? There's a<App>Battlerite for that. Matches are also much shorter than your typical MOBA. Think Rocket League for MOBA's. Pick it up, play a match for 10min and put it back down.....before you'd get through champ select in League.THE PRESENTATION/GRAPHICSLook I'll be real here, it's new, so it's not going to be as flashy as say DOTA 2 or LoL or HoTS. However, the Graphics are solid. (As I'm sure you can see, think WoW.) The character customization is also more extensive than most other mobas and is not hidden behind a paywall. (Think the reward system of Overwatch.) The only negative thing I will say here is that the music is nothing to write home about. It is pretty bland and generic, but then again I've never had the inclination to jam out to any other MOBA or Overwatch for that matter. Open up that Spotify account. Problem solved.THE ODEUM:(Credit to Ansvar for reminding me.)Battlerite features a sort of replay compendium called The Odeum which allows you to edit, view and post to the Battlerite community any awesome replay footage you might have or wish to see. You can search by user or browse a long list of upvoted plays. You can also view your own matches from a long list. This is especially helpful to those who wish to improve, as it allows you to critique yourself. It's also a nifty tool in case you want to prove you really did just 1v3 with that can of whoop♥♥♥♥♥mentioned earlier.OVERALL:I hope this game becomes the next big thing. The next League or CS: GO. It deserves it. It's worth the asking price just to support the devs who listen to their community and just genuinely care about their game. This game eliminates all the gripes I've ever had about MOBA's and then some. Some I didn't even realize I had before playing this. Supporting the devs or no, give this is a look at least when it's f2p and I'll see you in the stadium.FOR FURTHER INFORMATION:Please check out the comment section of this review as I answer some of the questions asked by the community!"
