,Recommended,504370,25634194,"Posted: 22 September, 2016",all,ModestLunatic,"So, this game is by Stunlock Studios, the folks behind Bloodline Champions. BLC is (was, I suppose) one of my favorite games of all time. It's one of the only online multiplayer games to actually get me to compete so intensely, to really desire to improve.BLC was a powerful combination of absolute skill based aiming, (even for melee attacks) fast paced gameplay, varied and pretty well balanced champions to play, and a heaping helping of SKILL CAP. The best BLC players were insanely better than even a pretty good player, but the magic was that they were using the same toolkit as somebody that had just started playing. That last bit wasn't true near the end of BLCs life, but I try to forget those times.Sorry, this isn't entirely on topic. Battlerite is not BLC, but Battlerite is the spiritual sequel to BLC, and it's my current hope that Battlerite gets popular enough to raise it to heights BLC never reached.Battlerite continues the charm of Stunlock's weird tribal art, absolute skill based aiming for every attack, and potentially blisteringly fast combat.They're attempting innovation with the ""Battlerite"" system, the ability to choose an enhancement for your champion after each round, up to 5 enhancements with 1 out of 3 per turn.How they balance their new Battlerite system will likely be key to if this game can usurp the glory days of BLC, but rest assured, I'll be there for this games future.Thanks for reading my disorganized rant! I'm bad at reviews. This game's future is important to me, so even if my writing is scattered, I want to voice my positivity for this game. It really is good, blind nostagia aside. It's extremely polished and fun for an Early Access game, and has managed to scratch that  BLC itch of mine that has been plaguing me for ages.Oh, and if you play and enjoy the game, please remember to give them feedback, as it is a beta, and remember to spread the word about the game as well. Battlerite is quite unique, so it shouldn't be too hard to sell some people on it."
