76561198141499280,Recommended,504370,30080608,Posted: 21 February,all,Nevasha,"After 250 hours of playing Battlerite, I've decided that it is finally time to write a review for this epic fighting masterpiece. While it has its pros and cons, Battlerite overall is a great game that is well on the way towards its ideal ""perfect"" state for its Free-To-Play launch. Please keep in mind that this review is based off of my opinions, and my views on the state of the game as a high diamond player.Pros:-Amazing gameplay-Intuitive mechanics-High skill cap-Effective counterplay for most scenarios-Polished game, no-low FPS lag-Clean and easy to distinguish what is happening-Large and continuously expanding character roster-Few cheaters/hackers-Cool cosmetics-Decently frequent updates-Extremely absorbing and addicting-Easy-to-enter tournaments-No snowballing (Always room for comeback)-100% skill and strategy, if you lose, you got outplayed. Maybe a matchup was unfavorable, but you personally could have played better.-Huge update coming soon (new gamemodes woot)-Odeum (playback games and post big plays, like an in-game instagram for sick outplays)-Very few bugs/glitchesCons:-Some characters are sometimes a bit too strong/meta-Small player base (Perhaps the biggest con, while the playerbase is good, matchmaking can sometimes feel way too long for a short 2v2 brawl.)-Ranking system (Recently got a change, and is a bit better, but still has tons of room for improvement)-Dev focus (Sometimes, it seems that the Devs are more excited to push out new cosmetics than improve balance or matchmaking)-Matchmaking (I still dont understand why I play with a bronzie against 2 Champions every now and then)These are most of the pros/cons I can think of off the top of my head, but overall this game is very fun and well made. Do keep in mind that Battlerite is still in early access, meaning not everything is perfect yet, but hopefully will be by the time of its full release. For $20, you get to play this awesome game many months earlier than the people waiting for F2P, as well as unlocking the full character cast (which means you dont have to grind up to buy characters). I highly reccomend this game to anyone who is at least a bit interested in it/anyone who enjoys MOBAs (Ex: LOL, Dota 2, HOTS, Smite), and give it my rating of 9/10. The Devs have room for improvement, but have already succeeded in making a kickass game for us to enjoy.See you in the arena. -Nevasha"
