,Recommended,504370,25607971,"Posted: 20 September, 2016",all,Минрад,"Alright, first off, I want to state: This is not a MOBA. There are no lanes, there is no farming, there are no items, there is no 50 minutes of positioning and planning, revolving around the occasional burst of action.Instead, this game is strictly those action parts. You slide down a gigantic suspended platform, the gates drop, and you burst into a small arena with a few walls and it's just you, your ally, two enemies, and you all want each other dead. It's snappy, everything feels responsive, and you have to land skillshots and make rapid decisions in a best of 5.This doesn't have the gigantic learning curve of DotA, where you're stuck wondering how to build your hero and select items and where to farm and how to cover the map. It's more like learning Smash Brothers: There's some combos you could learn, there's plenty of tech to learn so you feel yourself improving over time, and it's more about (quickly) learning how your and other champions behave. The meat of the gameplay comes down to coordinating with your teammates: there's huge rewards for proper positioning, cc chains, etc.All the core gameplay components have been laid out perfectly, and Stunlock's already laid out hints and teasers at plenty of new maps and heroes in the pipeline. As long as it can get some extra support in the form of tournaments and a better UI, I think this game has a bright and healthy future. Highly recommend trying it out, triply so if you've got a friend to play it with you!"
