,Recommended,504370,31203119,Posted: 17 April,all,Cambin,"*Update Edit* - A lot of negative reviews about 'stale development'. While it's been slow, it's Early Access so patience is required. Just today they announced the roadmap and F2P launch of 11/8. Please go read the ""Battlerite New Era"" news / update. Big things are coming for this game over the next few months, finally!The spiritual successor to Bloodline Champions, this game is a MOBA but not like League of Legends or SMITE. In Battlerite, you're pitted in an arena in a 2v2 or 3v3 setting and you battle it out until the last team, or person is standing. First team to win 3 takes the cake.The heroes are fun and many are challenging to learn and master. I can safely say that this is my favorite style of MOBA since there is no slow period of gameplay. You don't farm minions or lanes or gold. Your objective is to kill Poloma as fast as possible.I'm not the most skilled player in the world, but hitting skill shots feels extremely satisfying, especially when it's an Ultimate that results in a double kill or a clutch game 7 win. For $20 (was $14 during earlier EA) as an all-in price (includes all heroes, forever), there is no additional cost unless you want cosmetic items via the annoying trend of loot box roulette. You do earn plenty of chests via daily quests, leveling, etc... though so don't fret.As long as the playerbase holds up (my only real concern anymore), this game should stay relevant and fun. The studio is great at communicating updates and changes, which goes a long way with an ""Early Access"" tag. Though I would safely say this game doesn't feel like it is in EA anymore, so don't let that tag scare you.TLDR; Do you like MOBA's but don't care to farm minions? Do you enjoy team fights or duels? Do you enjoy having a good selection of heroes that feel unique and challenging? If yes to any of that, then give Battlerite a couple hours of effort.P.S. Shift key = EX ability modifier.8/10 - Very satisfying."
