,Recommended,504370,25809613,"Posted: 1 October, 2016",all,Paraakie Editor!,"Disclaimer: This game is in Early Access right now. A lot has already been updated and added in the few months this game has been out.  Thus even if the game was released right now (Decemner'16), it will feel and play like a full release game.Since the classic MOBAs (Dota2&LoL) hit the gaming scene, I was really hooked by the action based team-fights, I loved the skill-shots and the dodging, but really disliked everything else, Battlerite satisfies this hunger for epic team-fights and indepth combat. Those are achieved by picking one of  over 17 unique characters, which you bring to a small arena in a 2v2 or 3v3 death match. In a best of 5, lasting between 5 to 12 minutes, thereby removing the long time commitment and with it a lot of frustration.Exactly like the classic MOBAs, this game is played top-down and uses the fog of war really well, thus giving you, the player a lot of vision (more than dota2), to easily hit your abilities. Every character has a set of skills, but this game has more skills, in fact 9 skills per character. Usually one of these skills is a dodge skill, creating a lot of epic moments in 1v2 or 1v3 combacks. Although there are four powerful skills, that require energy, which is gained by using abilities and collecting energy on the map. One of skills often referred to as the Ultimate ability requires 100% energy, while the other skills requires only 25% of the energy, so a player always has to think about whether they want to wait for the Ultimate or if they rather use a skill now to get an advantage over the enemy.What I really like about the abilities is that the majority of them have some kind of debuff effect on the enemy or buff effect on you, by that giving every player great utility winning 1v2 fights. This utility can be further enhanced by the Battlerite upgrades you gain at the beginning of every round, but there are also some heal and damage options.So in conclusion the game is great. If the game is more fleshed out. I think this game will be worth playing once it's out as a Free-To-Play game. Or if you really want to try out the great gameplay and want to play with non-free-to-players, just get it now, the gameplay is already so good and satisfying.Note -> The game costs $US20 right now which giving access to all current and future characters, but will go free to play in the future."
