76561197986397211,Recommended,504370,25687931,"Posted: 25 September, 2016",all,HekaDooM,"Is it a MOBA? No.No laning or farming to gain exp/gold to ""become powerful"" enough to fight. No item system to force-synergise your spells. No team mates feeding during laning, destroying your efforts of becoming farmed/levelled enough to participate in fights.Just skill here, kids. Scoop out all of the early-game detritus of a MOBA and add those sweet, sweet teamfights that you farm and level for but in a more concentrated form. No levelling or farming required here, you start as the best you can possibly be and so do your enemy. Battlerites alter abilities but their general use remains similar. If you lose, it is because your team lacked the skill to win.Hard to throw blame in circumstances like these.Positioning is crucial. Did you use that large jump move to enter combat? Well now it is on cooldown and you're without an escape mechanism if the proverbial hits the fan. Are you being too cautious? Well now you are too far from the fight to effectively deal damage or support your allies.Reflexes are crucial. Do you activate your counter in the hopes an enemy will clumsily attack you? Are you that enemy, and will you clumsily attack or see the counter animation and cancel your movement? Are you the healer watching the scenario unfold, and can you effectively shield/heal as required when the event resolves?Hand-eye coordination is crucial. Can you hit an opponent consistently at various distances and speeds with differing projectiles and aoe vectors? Can you do this with the knowledge they could counter, leap, teleport or just plain change direction at any time? The potential for mindgames is great here.If you have the patience to learn and the above has interested you, this game....is crucial. I've played almost 20 hours and witnessed no community toxicity. The graphics and sound are great, no oversaturation of particle effects to make the game cluttered, and the developers are on the ball with updates and general community activity.""...wait, he's only played ~20 hours?""Yes, and I am still learning myself. But be sure to check back. I'm hooked. That ~20 hours is only going to rise and rise...."
