76561198054167328,Recommended,504370,25665234,"Posted: 24 September, 2016",all,SteveRaptor,"This is a great Top down arena hero brawl.Its easy to get into but hard to master, pure skill based combat with short matches.Very polished and optimized, so far I have yet to encounter a bug or a problem.The heroes feel very balanced and there is no rock- paper- scissor in the game, so you can master your favourite hero and play mostly with him without the worry of getting counter picked, the outcome of the battles depends on your skill, reflexes and outsmarting your opponents.As someone who so far never joind a pre-made, this game is very solo friendly, it offers two modes:,2v2 and 3v3.I guess that 3v3 is better going organized but 2v2 is very friendly for solo queue, I have over 50 matches and I have yet to get stomped or stomp someone, you have enough impact to win a game even when outnumbered and your ally woke up on the wrong side of the bed.Regarding the community, so far, except 1-2 games, the players are nice and polite, except maybe one time, I never encountered a salty or rude players on my team or the enemy team, no ""GG EZ"" and all that bs, which is a plus.Most of the games are farily balanced and not one sided, which is great and doesn't leave you with a feel of frustration even if you lose.The only Cons I can point is the lack of quick match (non-ranked games), you can not test and learn new champions vs other players.You can only do that vs the AI (which puts out a good fight in most cases).Also the cosmetics feels very lackluster, the only difference in most of them are the colors, even on the most rare ones.If you like the combat aspect of MOBAS in an arena style gameplay or a fan of the WoW arena combat, then this game is for you.Highly recommended.9/10"
