76561198015688762,Recommended,504370,25835004,"Posted: 3 October, 2016",all,QPON,"Battlerite... I'll tell you one thing Stunlock Studios did that was right... and that was leaving FunCom, never looking back at that travesty of a game publisher, and going back to their roots. They're a brilliant team of game developers, they do a damn good job at PvP. They've got years and years under their belts, and I'm so happy they managed to recooperate from the stranglehold Funcom had on them for a while. Not many other game developers are so lucky.Well enough about the studio, now to look at the game.Polished.That's one word I would use to describe the overall feel of the game. It's absolutely, very well made and you can tell that this was made by a very passionate team.This game was being developedfor a much longer than most people know. A lot of people will come to it without knowing the rich history behind Battlerite, and how a game like this could spring up out of nowhere. Without absolutely no bugs this game runs perfectly, it has impressive graphics and physix beating games like LoL and DoTA2 in that department as well.Gameplay:Fast-paced(at times calling it fast-paced is an understatement),addictive,  andexhilarating.There are a lot of factors that come to play when trying to explain why this game is so addictive, but it really just dwindles down to the fact that it's incredibly satisfying, and it's pulse-pounding fun. Meaning you're gonna get into some matches and by the end of it you'll be sweatin', you'll be shakin, but you're still gonna be shootin! and you're still gonna be gettin those KO's, you're adrenaline kicks in and your visual acuity sharpens, you reactions times enhance and you're on fire! and  you feel that fire and once you're outta the match you wanna hop in for another go at it. It's hard to stop at times.Best part being that you don't need to dredge through 20 minutes of building up and dealing with terrible team mates or toxic people arguing for those 20 minutes and then ANOTHER 20 minutes while you either win or lose and leave the game feelin' like you wasted tons of time, unsatisfied. Somehow that appeals to a large amount of people I guess, but this is the game for people who want to be spared the tedium once and for all and place a PVP game that's everything they've always wanted. This is REAL Arena combat.There's a rewarding ""Grade"" system as you progress you grade higher and you faces better players who are also that high. Think of it like a ratings system. It works fine by me, the people at the top are definitely, INCREDIBLY good players, in a league of their own for sure.Speaking of rewards, there are a lot of cosmetic items in this game and those are the only thing that you can buy with money. But the cool thing is that you can also earn them through chests that you earn through completeing quests which are long th lines of ""Win 6 Games"", I think you get the idea. I like this because those people who can't afford it can still customize and feel like they're earning new stuff. I'm sure they'll add exclusive items for those who spend the money but that's fair, they need to support themselves somehow.Community:So far I haven't encountered any toxicity in this game besides Croak and Lucie (ehh ehh, get it?! cuz they use poisons! hahaha...anyway) - It's all been pleasant thus far, helpful players, sharing tips, grouping up after matches and playing together, adding one another to friends, although I'm a generally friendly guy in games like these nowadays so I usually spark up small chat and if they're good players and we're on the same par skill wise I'll add them for future play or playing right then and there.Battlerite also has an automatic recording feature that lets you go to past games you've played, replay them and even edit and publish them for everyone else to see. They let you go pretty dang far back which is really impressive.  I wish every other pvp game out there had a system like this (talkin bout you SMITE!) but they don't. Just another way SLS is steppin it up. I know other games do this but not for all matches and nowhere near as far in the past. I did leave some feedback for them talking about cool features to add to it so maybe they'll do it.Overall:Stunlock Studios has really nailed it when it comes to the Arena PVP formula. They've got it down to a science, they know how to make it satisfying on many different levels, the combat, the mechanics, the physics/graphics, the rewards, the social aspects. They've done it! And they're not done yet! I know for sure we've all got a lot of cool stuff on the way. SLS won't let us down now that they've taken the reins again!Anyway -- It's time for me to crash since It's 1AM and I was tryin to go to bed by 11...but I got stuck on Battlerite... lol this is something I should probly get used to soon."
