,Recommended,504370,26238863,"Posted: 26 October, 2016",all,Rexter,"Battlerite.This game is to me, extreme amounts of fun. If you are familiar with games such as League of Legends, Dota 2 or any other game of the ""MOBA"" genre then this game might be fun for you.What is Battlerite?Battlerite is a fast paced MOBA now, don't let the term ""MOBA"" put you off as this is unlike the others. Instead of the traditional three lanes and jungle set up this game has an enclosed arena enviroment. This game is a 2v2 or 3v3 first to 3 rounds based system where it is possible to make very good comebacks which keeps the gameplay competitive and you always feel like you have a chance. There is not outscaling or feeding power in this game, everyone is always on an equal playing field.Why do I recommend Battlerite?I recommend Battlerite because this game is tons of fun. It's never ending teamfights. It's like skipping to the 40 minute mark of league where everyone is full build and you're actually starting to have fun because you're playing at full power. I also recommend this game because it's very fast paced and matches don't take long at all due to a sudden death mechanic which makes the arena create a shrinking death zone which does high amounts of damage over time.For me this game is a10/10, it's absolutly perfect for me."
