,Recommended,504370,25907342,"Posted: 7 October, 2016",all,Dan,"I'm a big buff black ogre who beats people with a bolt of chicken.10/10.But really though, this game is definitely worth the buy, just remember it will go F2P later but paying to have all champions in the future AND support the Battlerite team is worth it 100%.I actually swore off of MOBAs before buying Battlerite because I have a bit of an anger problem with them.. (OKAY, a HUGE anger problem with them..) BUT, Battlerite's gameplay is so much fun I don't even feel mad when I lose. Only when I make mistakes is when I get a little upset but hey it's part of the gameplay.Pretty much imagine team fighting without all the buildup, imagine a GvG situation in an MMO, the feeling of seeing your opponents and the suspence of who will make the first move.. ALL OF THAT wrapped up in a small arena.The only cons I can think of are obvious ones:-Learning Curve: There is one. How steep it is depends on your playstyle. If you only play one champion, you'll have to learn what others do through battle and that can be a bit rough, the higher your rank gets. If you play all the champions(which you should because there are daily quests which give rewards for playing certain ones), you'll learn every champions moveset through experience and knowing is half the battle.. LITERALLY. Knowing what every champion can do is THE MOST IMPORTANT skill in Battlerite to learn. One I current am very ignorant of. But it's not a huge learning curve, there's even AI matches and training arenas to help if you just want to test champions out, so.. yeah!-Matchmaking: It's not perfect. No games Matchmaking can be perfect. However, in the future I imagine this will be ironed out. This is Early Access anyway. When it goes F2P I imagine this will help with a surge of new players to have more close games. But I feel the game's matchmaking is pretty decent.TL;DR: Team Fights. 2v2/3v3. Fun.PLAY THIS GAME NOW. You won't regret it."
