,Recommended,504370,28133937,"Posted: 1 December, 2016",all,Scav3ngeR,"This game takes all the good teamfighting/skirmising elements from various MOBA's and combines them in a way that makes the game action-packed and quick.I obviously cannot comment on the balance of the game as of yet, but it does seem quite fair. The maps are small, however they allow you to out-maneuver opponents with the fog of war (which in my opinion is done very well). This lets the game not feel overbearing if you're ever in a melee vs. ranged situation.The battlerite system is super satisfying. It gives you a good sense of growth and intensity when you get access to better rites later into the game. The best of 5 format is the best format that I would imagine for the game. Getting a reverse sweep is beautiful.Rather than talking about cons, I would like to remind you that while I definitely advise people to purchase this game if they're a fan of the teamfighting aspect of MOBA's, that it is in early access, so bugs and minor balance issues are to be expected. I'll likely come back to discuss the cons and what can be improved with more playtime.I really like this game and would like to see it grow, so give it a shot if you love all-out brawls.*There needs to be more options for customising your game experience.*The in-game ability descriptions should tell you whether an ability is a line skillshot or an area ability, just because it makes it easier to understand.I* would personally like a clear distinction between what can and cannot go over walls in the game.*The center orb could use a visual indicator when its about to explode (or if there is already one, make it more obvious. I haven't seen it.)*The ability to browse through the client while in queue would be nice. You can't really do anything but look at your own characters abilities. Being able to look at other champs and open chests would be great.*Area-cast abilities could use a max cast range indicator.*Further steam integration (inviting, adding) would be nice*Spectating friends could be cool. Maybe a spectate higher ranked players option?"
