,Recommended,504370,29553915,Posted: 28 January,all,Kuuhaku,"Battlerite is often described as a MOBA without the creeps/jungle/towers/items, and that's relatively accurate. But I think the better description would be a top-down version of World of Warcraft arena. It certainly reminds me more of the latter than the former, mostly because of the pacing (Battlerite matches aren't quite as quick as the typical MOBA teamfight), but also because each character has more abilities than your typical MOBA character.This game is all about positioning, teamwork, skillshot aim, and timing. It's extremely satisfying, and there's a ton of opportunity to outplay your opponents. When it's working right, there's almost zero danger of the typical MOBA ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥t occurring. What I'm referring to are things like being perma-CC'd, or taken from 100%-0% health inside of a single stun, or having battles that go on forever because the healers are just able to keep everyone topped off. The game's systems work in such a way as to discourage or outright prevent all of that, and that's really refreshing.Definitely worth the purchase if you're sick of any of the stuff I just described, or you're bored of WoW arenas."
