,Recommended,504370,27937278,"Posted: 28 November, 2016",all,FabianBlaha MT,"When I hear people call this a MOBA, comparing it to LoL and Dota, it hurts.It does NOT have lanes.It does NOT have creeps.It does NOT have objectives like towers and inhibitors.It does NOT have games that lasts 40 minutes.It does NOT have items and currency in a match.This is as much a MOBA as Overwatch and Quake Champions is. It has different characters, the similarity pretty much stops there.What Battlerite is, is a 2v2/3v3 fast paced arena brawler. The games takes about 10 minutes or less to finish, and the match mostly consists of map control and fighting to the death. If you die, your out. No respawning. Every move, ability and damage point matters. First to three wins, walks out of the game as champions.You move with WASD, and you have 7+2 abilities. And they are all skill shots. Yes, you can NOT click on an enemy and attack, you gotta aim every single attack and ability, all while positioning your self properly.Safe to say, it was a bit confusing at first. But once I got the hang of it, it was so fun and rewarding to land shots, space out abilities to kite perfectly and positioning my self so I don't just die every time.But even still, I feel like I'm only scratching the surface of mastering this game.Yes, I recommend this title. But with the consideration that it is in fact Early Access, it has some big flaws like balancing, poor matchmaking and questionable hitboxes. But with some more work, and a bigger player base, I can definitely see this become one of the big competitive ""easy to learn, but hard to master"" games out there.And with that said, I'm gonna play some more right now!"
