76561198048802572,Recommended,504370,26072630,"Posted: 16 October, 2016",all,Vanerac,"Super duper good game. Most fun I've had playing a team battle style game ever. And I've played a lot a League, a lot of Overwatch, a little Smite, and a touch of Dota 2. Probably in my top 3 competitive games of all time right now, sitting next to Rocket League and Super Smash Bros Melee. It's only 2v2s and 3v3s, which means you realistically only need one good friend to have the game to have a crapload of fun destroying people. Plus, everything you do in the game is skill based, so there is tons of room for outplay potential. There are no bs instant point and click abilities or anything. Everything is about hitting your skillshots, dodging enemy skillshots, keeping track of everybody's cooldowns and going ham when your enemy has busted their outs.All in all, a brilliantly designed game, well worth the money (I've certainly had way more than $20 worth of fun, and I've only had the game for a couple weeks) very well polished, good balance (and hopefully they will continue to tweak it as the meta develops) and just downright enjoyable. 10/10 would recommend"
