76561198005653808,Recommended,504370,25706459,"Posted: 26 September, 2016",all,Flak Maniak,"Battlerite is good. Really good. Of course, I would say that, given Bloodline Champions was my favorite game, ever. If you want a fast-paced multiplayer battling game, Battlerite is for you. Tired of forty-minute-long matches that are decided at the twenty minute mark? Tired of last-hitting minions for ten minutes? Tired of squabbling over farm and kills with your teammates? Well, Battlerite's for you. This game is played in short rounds. (1-2 minutes.) You will play best of five rounds. So even a whole match is much shorter than a game of your favorite MOBA. Also, the two game formats are 2v2 and 3v3, so it's easy to put together a team. Because the game is divided into rounds, if your team makes horrible mistakes, instead of sitting there for twenty minutes suffering, you can just figure out what you did wrong, then go and win the next round. Also, instead of an overall slow pace but with moments that are almost too fast to follow, Battlerite has a relenetlessly quick pace.Really, though, the reason to like Bloodline Champions is how the core gameplay works. You move with WASD and aim all your abilities. Because of this, there are a lot of mind games. You have to guess where your opponent will be a fraction of a second from now. Also, there are lots of counter moves, intensifying the need to predict your opponents. In this game, you can't just get in range and land guaranteed damage. It's much more fighting game-like than those games where you right click your opponent. If you want a game that's really action-y, this game is for you. If you just want to battle, this game is for you. If you want a game full of depth and subtlety and room to grow as a player, this game is for you."
