,Recommended,504370,25934172,"Posted: 8 October, 2016",all,Lilla Kyckling,"Battlerite is a mix of the World of Warcraft arena, the adrenaline of a 1v1 fighter like Mortal Kombat or Street fighter and the character style of a MOBA like league of legends or DOTA 2.It's well wort your attention and you should really try it out if you have ever played any of the above. Already in early acces it's a balanced and competitive experience.The gameplay is fast and rewarding, there is no RNG wich means that if you are better than your opponent you can and  will kick their♥♥♥♥♥ The 2v2 format is perfect for a ""solo que"" system as it makes teamplay possible whilst minimizing the chanses for afks or trolls. It also gives your actions much more meaning and bigger consequences. If you play bad in Battlerite you are going to lose because you're half your team whilst in a game like LoL or DOTA 2 where there are 5 players in each team you can still get carried if you play bad and you can still lose even if you play good.The characters are designed in a way that allowes for outplays to happen. There are no fixed abillities (other than shields) and everything can be dodged. Majority of caracters also have ways of becoming ""imaterial"" or ignoring all effects for a small period of time.There are many ""trances"" or counters that make your caracter enter a state where if you get hit by a projectile or melee strike you get a benefite. This allows for great moments and mindgames as you try to trick your opponent into using their trance and get them to trigger yours. All this and more makes winning feel rewarding as you can clearly tell how you played better than your opponent.I have personally felt in love with this game after spending the last 6 years playing League of Legends. This game has been really refreshing for me because of how little time you spend waiting for things. Playing a game of league takes so long and is filled with so much nothing. In battlerite farming is replaced with fighting, walking form lane to lane is replaced with trying to get the last hit of the middle orb befor the enemy, watching your allies carry you for 20 minutes after a lost laningphase never happens because there is no laningphase or snowballing as that would ruin the competitivness, instead of getting smashed to pieces by a vayne your bot lane fed you are picking the right battlerite for the next round after you lost the last because of a stupid misstake your never going to do again. All there is is fighting. Positioning, outsmarting, maximising damage and settign up cc combos with your friend is all you do. And it never gets old.The negatives for me have been the lack of progression. You have a level on each caracter that you can level up to ten but the rewards haven't been to intriguing. There is no way of showing of these levels either and the time it takes to get a caracter to level ten isn't to long. A simple fix would be to take away the cap of the levels and let you brag about it in some way. Otherwise there is really nothign but the ranking system to progress through. As far as I know there have been no talk about a progression system either unfortunatly.What keeps me playing is the rewarding feeling of playing better than the other guy.Over all I hope you give this game a try when it is released and becomes free to play in early 2017."
