,Recommended,504370,28282760,"Posted: 9 December, 2016",all,Doc Stalin,"DOC STALIN'S REVIEWPROS-Short 15 min maximum games (usual game lasts around 10 minutes)-Very high skill ceiling-Get all the champions free forever-Gameplay is clean as ♥♥♥♥-Great servers (have DC'd once during my play time and it was my one internet)-Each character has so much depth to them and none of them suck-Constant Updates-Extreme Clarity with the Devs-All in game purchases are purely cosmeticCONS- The UI could use some work but the devs have addressed that already- Tutorial is not clear at all and does not go over a lot of very important parts of the game (this means you need to spend a lot of your own time looking this♥♥♥♥♥♥up - I don't mind because I love the game but again I feel they will fix this in time)- Again this is not really a problem for long but the game doesn't have the best ranking system- You can get queued with people that just plain aren't anywhere near your skill level but then again there isn't many players currently.- All the issues I am addressing here are almost non problems  because the devs have addressed that they want to fix them.GAMEPLAYThe gameplay of this game could not get any better. The overall experience is clean as ♥♥♥♥ . NO ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥t RNG. All skill and CD based combat. All the champions feel unique and alive. The core gameplay doesn't have any glaring issues that are noteworthy. The only gameplay issue to date is that the skill shot notifications aren't the most erucate. Hard to read sometimes if you are going to get hit. But given these Devs this will be fixed eventually.The champion pool is under three categories. All the champions are rather unique but some of the ideas carry over to other champions such as counters. The first being ranged. Ranged champions as you would think are just champions that their main auto attack is a range ability. They have different mechanics such as a bow that shoots slower but hits harder and a shotgun that does spread damage and damage per bullet.  I would recommend playing Jade to understand the mechanics down for most ranged champions (again personal opinion). The second category is melee. This is as you would think their auto attacks are within melee range. This does not mean they have no ranged abilities. Also their ranged weapons have different ranges based on the champion.The last category is Support. This is mostly based on the fact they have a heal built into their main abilities.I will not go huge into mechanics of this game because this is a review and I just wanted to give you a snapshot.CONTENTThe game currently only has 14 champions last time I counted. They are adding new ones at the moment at least 1 or 2 every month which is pretty damn good for this type of arena game.There are loot boxes similar to other games. They each drop 3 items. The first type is the silver chest which you can only acquire by playing the game(quests, playing a champion repeatedly, etc). This chest is pretty easy to come by and will give you a base start but can drop some sweet stuff. The second chest is the gold chest which costs in game currency of 500 gold which can take a few hours to get. These chests can also be purchased with real money in bulk amounts.  The last chest is the Legendary chest which is only able to get by leveling up a champions(you get levels by playing them). There are certain events that might throw one in there as a bundle like they did for the last champ that came out.FINAL SCORE9.5 / 10Overall one of the best games I have played hands down. Great to pick up at any point and just play a couple of games then head out for the day. Devs are clear on their intentions which doesnt happen often. Buy this game and don't look back. I am by no means a pro at this game but hit me up if you want to play sometime!Thanks for reading!"
