,Recommended,504370,28718630,"Posted: 27 December, 2016",all,Blink,"Battlerite combines elements of MOBA combat, arena pvp and shooters. The game has a top-down camera, a handful of unique abilities for each of the diverse cast of heroes, and ""battlerites"" which are hero-specific talents that you choose  after each round of a best of 5. The result is an incredibly fun, fast-paced, fluid 2v2/3v3 competitive pvp game.PROS:-Well designed, skill based combat-Unique heroes, good aesthetics-Nothing pay to win in the chests-Seemingly large and supportive community for the future of the game-Practice mode to try out heroes already implemented, as well as botsNEUTRAL:-PvP Only-High skillcap, fast pacedCONS:- Competitive ranking system could still use some work (devs seem to be actively trying to figure it out)- A lot of the skins just look like recolorsDespite being in early access, the gameplay is smooth and the visuals are nice. The heroes are all charming and well designed. For the most part, the skillset of each hero feels unique, although the different classes tend to blend together a bit. There is a chest-reward system incorporated into leveling up that gives various cosmetics such as skins, poses and weapon skins.All in all, a very well done PvP-centric game that looks to have a promising future. Highly recommended."
76561197968455387,Recommended,504370,26025456,"Posted: 14 October, 2016",all,[CZ]Kaizen,"Battlerite is everything I ever wanted out of the Diablo 3 arena that never came.I played Bloodline Champions early on in release and had a ton of fun, but it was a little too chaotic for my taste with up to 5 man teams. Battlerite is essentially an updated version of the same, but beautifully focused on quick 2v2 and 3v3 matches, AND has the added benefit of not being managed by Funcom.From what I understand the game will be F2P upon release, but honestly WELL worth the asking price even now in early access. I haven't had this much fun with a new game in so long. Some of the social features and the UI could use some work, but haven't taken away from my experience thus far.Pros-Customization (Both Cosmetics and from in-game Battlerites that effect combat)-Quick and Exciting Matches-Replay System with functionality to edit and share-PvP and PvE (Including Private matches where you invite your friendsCons-Early Access (There are a few bugs here and there, but none have been game-breaking)-Audio Issues (Possibly just an early access problem, but once in a while everything will get really distorted)-Skin Customization is a little thin at the moment-UI needs improvementI HIGHLY recommend this game as I have been depriving myself of sleep for days on end now just to play it.Please don't ruin your life like I have."
