,Recommended,504370,25705059,"Posted: 25 September, 2016",all,Dewsader,"*MY EARLY ACCESS/BETA REVIEW* Battlerite is in essence a moba, but don't think ""Oh so it's like League of Legends/Dota?"" No no no, it's more than that. It's some of the fastest most entertaining combat I've ever encountered (Besides Bloodline Champions of course which is the game this is based off of) The skill ceiling of this game is ridiculously high to the point where no two matches feel the same. The cast of characters is somewhat small as of now, yes but the devs are working to add more and it's exciting. To all of my friends or anyone who is thinking about buying into the early access, I'd say go for it. It was more than worth my money(Especially seeing as how the value of the early access pack is really high since you get all characters current and future.)Edit: I normally don't write huge reviews but for this game I kind of have to so here we go.This game is fantastic there's nothing else to really say that does it glory. The idea of the game is magnificent in the fact that it shows potential to be a great esport after some balance patches and etc. There's a reason the game wasn't released to the public as of yet. The game does need some polish. There's some strange bugs a not that great ranking system, no normal games and a whole slew of things that would turn so many people off right away. But don't let that stop you. The devs are constantly working and constantly listening to the complaints of the community to make a great game for everyone. The content seems boring at first sight (According to some people I've tried to show it to.) But it's quite interesting since the game never feels like the same game. After one round is completed you have a set of options that allow you to play the game with as much freedom as you want. The whole idea is to give players options that are all good and all useful. Plus the skill ceiling makes it all the better. You can play the game and constantly improve. Grasping the basics WILL be a little tough. You WILL hit into every counter. You WILL miss a lot. There's no saying you'll pick up this game and be a god at it instantly. But there's so much more to the game. Push through the frustration of sucking and a whole world is opened to you. That's all thanks for reading~"
