,Recommended,504370,26068789,"Posted: 16 October, 2016",all,Sonto,"Battlerites is a team-based Arena brawler that is the spiritual successor of Bloodline champions which is effectively the same game by Stunlock studios.It's a best of 5 rounds fighting game that's played 2v2 or 3v3. That's it. That's all there is.You start the client, pick a champ, hop into an arena, beat 2 or 3 peasants a few times and let the cycle begin anew.They have announced that it will become Free 2 Play with micro-transactions for cosmetic upgrades because, and I'm probably quoting the sales executive on the board meeting in which this decision took place, ""it worked for League of Legends"". The cosmetics are also unlockable through an ingame currency which you earn by playing.The game also tries really hard to be an E-sport, so we should judge it as one.First of all, there is a suprising mechanical depth behind the brawling, which makes watching a match as a player really engaging as well. The battles are tightly action-packed with enough overview to have an idea of what's going on. On top of that, the titular perks, that upgrade one of your abilities, chosen as a new round starts make for an interesting strategic draft.The immediate downside is that this very depth also makes the game hard to explain to anyone who hasn't played it before without crashing their brainserver with ridiculous amounts of onunderstandable gibberish. It's the computergame equivalent of talking soccer with your wife.That being said, I really like playing the game. The mechanics and maps are balanced enough to always have a way to outplay your opponents and I've always liked skirmishing over macro-wavecontrol anyway. If you're a player vs player - player then Bloodline Champions 2 is definitely a must-have for your gamelibrary."
