76561198073904210,Recommended,504370,26289090,"Posted: 29 October, 2016",all,Naalith,"I've never been so quick to jump to recommending a game. I've played nearly every MOBA on the market, have over 8000 games on LoL and still play it every day, play Smite, play HotS, played Awesomenauts, played DotA. On top of that I am super into team based games like Overwatch and Paladins. Maybe it's my experience from so many other games in the genre but I've never been so pleasantly surprised by a game right from the beginning. Firstly, this isn't like any other MOBA. Some might argue that it isn't even a MOBA. Items, minion farming, draft pick, and currency systems have all been stripped from the game. Don't let that scare you off like it did me for a few weeks, because this game has refined short, punchy combat to perfection.Firstly, the map is extremely small and the center has healing orbs and things that charge your ult (ults charge similarly to Overwatch and Paladins, hitting enemies and healing allies charges it faster, or use the orbs in the middle of the map.) This means that if a team gets pushed from the center, they are at a disadvantage and can fall behind, leading to a sense of urgency to fight in the center of the map.Secondly, the games are short. While many people, myself included, may find other MOBAs to be a more epic and full experience with tons of intricacies, the low end for a time investment in those games is 20 minutes. In League and DotA, games can stretch upwards of an hour and even go over at times. This game is perfect for if you want to jump out and into games super quickly. Victory is achieved by one team winning 3 rounds by eliminating all other players. Each round after 2 minutes, the sides of the Arena become dark and begin to close in. Soon only the center of the map remains, and people outside the center of the map will take massage damage per second until they die. This means each round will only go, at most, two and a half minutes. However, this doesn't cheapen the experience at all. The rounds are adrenaline filled and super punchy and surreal. A single person can outplay the other team with an ult and crazy wins and comebacks can happen like when the opposing team has two rounds won, and you need to win all three to win the whole match.Thirdly, the combat is just fantastic. Each character feels full of intricacy and is difficult to master to the full extent of their power, like any good competetive game. Each character has a defensive ability, ultimate, and what I called charged abilities. Charged abilities use a quarter of your ult's charge to do a more powerful attack on a standard ability, or you can use a quarter ult charge to use an extra spell that isn't normally available. This means you have to carefully manage your energy. Are you the last man on your team alive in a 1v2? Are you sure in that situation you can charge your full ult? Are you sure your full ult will even be more beneficial to you winning than four charged abilities with extra effects? At the start of each round, each character also gets to choose a Battlerite, which enchants an aspect of your character. For example, a character I play has an extremely high slow for 1.5 seconds, but on round one I like to take a Battlerite that turns the slow into a root. This means instead of people weaseling their way out by walking or using a movement ability, they are stuck in place and my team can better jump on them and kill them. With up to 5 rounds in each game and 3 Battlerites chosen per round, you can adapt your character to what you need in each game depending on who you are up against. These decisions have to be made quickly, on the fly, and a mess up could cost you your like.Finally, speaking of a mess up costing you your life, that is perhaps the greatest strength of this game. Winning is based entirely upon your skill as a player and your skill as a team. With no items, no leveling, and no hidden runes or masteries outside the game like in many other MOBAs, the game is completely balanced unless you choose the wrong Battlerite for the situation (still your fault) or make a mistake in the course of a fight. Death is permanent each round, die and you are out until the next round comes around. Dive too hard and you might get stunned and killed instantly. Stay back too long while your team goes in and they might die 2v3 without you. Miss an ult or use a charged attack at the wrong time, making you unable to use your ult, you know the drill. One of the first games a friend and I played in a 2v2 matchup we were playing against people who had chosen the same characters at us, and we ended up going to round 5 with two wins on each team. The last round was extremely intense, but we coordinated our attacks on our opponents and barely beat them with one of us dead and the other about two hits from dying. It may literally have been one of the biggest adrenaline rush I've ever felt in a game, and that's saying a lot after having played so many other competetive games. Individual skill matters here, the only objective is to kill the other team and there won't be ""fed"" enemies coming and killing you with a three item lead like in other games. It sounds simplistic, but the combat is so intricate that it never feels that way in the heat of the short rounds. Leveling characteres and completing quests give you access to purely cosmetic items, similar to Overwatch, and every character is unlocked from the start so there is no pay to win.Overall, the game is just great, and if you love competitive games like me you will be hard pressed to find a better $20 purchase to feed your addiction. If you are one to avoid early access I can understand that, but just know this isn't your Rust or DayZ that need patches to feel fun after years of being on the market, this game is already worth it in its current state. The game feels complete and I'm sure they'll continue to add new skins, characters, and maps up to and after launch. Get some friends to buy it with you and the experience is even better, but even solo the game is fantastic. If you are still on the fence, this game has quite the following on Twitch and you can check out the gameplay for yourself. For short, adrenaline filled competitive matches it doesn't get much better than this.Update, I've played about 30 hours since this review, and it is still awesome."
