,Recommended,504370,25678770,"Posted: 24 September, 2016",all,Racket is a racket is a racket,"I'll be frank, I dont write alot of reviews on steam and if I do they're probably satire.This game however deserves a proper review because it just hit's all the nerves I've been looking for.From first glance you can probably tell this is moba-like, it has some pretty well fleshed out champions and map design.The combat system is similar to any other MOBA you can expect, however the made difference is the length of games and the lack of a farming/minion system; which is by no means a bad thing, because to me it's a great thing!.You jump into this arena and begin bashing no need to have a laning phase or anything of the sort. You can't fall behind because you're terrible at farming and you can't feel like someone has an OP champion because every champion is already unlocked for you! The rounds are best of 5s which a max limit of 2 minutes per a round so your games will only be 10 minutes maximum. The combat mechanics are quite interesting as there is no real burst aside from ults and even those wont obliterate you so you dont have to worry about getting insta-killed as there is always going to be enough headroom to react to a situation. Overall I would highly recommend this game and I would write more to this review if I wasnt so darn lazy."
