,Recommended,504370,31328465,Posted: 23 April,all,AsCii_exe,"Normally I don't like MOBAs that don't have long matches like LoL or DOTA because when the match ends I always feel like it was too short or that it ends just when the fun part begins but I never got that feeling with this game because every match is more like playing intense mid-game teamfights but your allies and enemies get switched every 15 minutes and  there's really no thing like ""early"" and ""late"" game, even though you still have a match progress, at the start of each round you choose a ""Battlerite"" that's basically a perk that upgrades something for some of your skills like ""now this also silences on hit"" or ""this will heal more"" but also very oftenly things that add an entire new layer of depth to a skill.When I had a few hours in I started to soloQ ranked only and the community is fantastic, well... silver and low gold are swarmed with flamers, specially low gold-high silver (bronzes were pretty chill though), I really recommend you to disable the chat until you reach plat which is actually really easy because until you dont reach high-gold a win gives you 3 times more points than what a lose takes away and when you reach gold 2/higher everyone is really really nice, I never saw a flamer in any game ever since I got into plat, at max someone a bit salty about me failing sometimes but never more than thatAll champs are in general fun to play with and balanced, as in any other MOBA there are a few ones that are very annoying to go against like Pearl and Croak but Pearl is known as the strongest healer in the entire game and Croak is you traditional mobile assassin but I dont think neither of them is broken. One general thing that I would say about the champion pool is that 90% of them are insanely mobile no matter their role every single one of them with 1 to 4 movement skills like dashes, jumps, movespeed buffs, etc and I can cound with one hand the number of champs with only one movement skill, ironically enough I think almost all of them are the weakest champs atm.The only con I could see is the fact that it's an early access so there's not a lot of champions and the game can get kind of repetitive if you don't enjoy being a One Trick Pony, not my case though and the fact that the game has 14 perks per champ + 8 skills make all of them quite deep and mechanically intensive so you'll always have something to improve or a new build to try with your mainIn general I would recommend buying it, specially if you have some friend to duoQ with but if you are not really into MOBAs or don't have so much that one trick pony spirit I would wait for it to get out of early access or for some good sale to come up."
