76561198000799183,Recommended,504370,31223640,Posted: 18 April,all,ArmoredBras,"Battlerite is what you get when you keep only the good PvP parts from a mmorpg or a moba, is fast paced action with the right balance of skill, precision and strategy.[ GAMEPLAY ]It's not the easiest competitive game to jump in at first, each character have 6 unique abilities (+ basic attack) which might not seem a lot, but when put in battle for the first times is easy to forget which one does what and it often result in spamming your way through the first maches (which is fun nontheless).  It doesn't take long though to get a grip on a character and on the general way you should play the game. In any case is clear that the skill ceiling for this game is very high which is a good thing.At the moment there are 20 different characters and they are in my opinion all beatifully crafted, there isn't one that is boring or shallow, some of them are more easier at first but all of them are pretty hard to master to perfection. Also, the twist of this game is that any match is composed of 3-5 rounds and at the start of each of them you get to chose 1 of 3 pre-determined upgrades for your abilities (called ""Battlerites""), this allows you to craft a slightly different strategy or playstyle for each match depending on your needs (damage, surivability, mobility, etc). This upgrade system is well though and increases the gameplay depth by a good amount. Another intresting choice is the use of the fog of war for both enemies and allies, I really wasn't expecting it but I find it very refreshing.So, the gameplay (in my opinion) is on point, maybe it will not suit your taste, but it seems clear what the devs wanted to achieve with this game and I personally think they did it.The only thing I can really complain about is the lack of an ingame signal system like ""go there"", ""danger in that spot"" or ""kill that guy"". It's not essential but sometimes I feel the need to comunicate this way (maybe because I'm used to play Lol).[ GAME BALANCE ]In regards of the game balance it seemed to me at first that some characters were more powerfull than others, but after many more hours of play I'm not sure anymore which is supposedly stronger, every match is clear that the ability of the player to use it trumps everything else by a long shot. Some character are for sure (at least a bit) stronger than others because balancing this kind of games is very tricky, but I think this can really show only when top players are competing.[ MATCH MAKING ]The matchaking system is fine, the wait times are pretty short (a couple of minutes usually) for both 2v2 and 3v3, I never had connection or lag problems and is rare to find toxic people. Even when good and bad players get paired together is unusual to witness strong verbal abuse.The thing I would like to be changed though is the fact that you cna't queue as 2 for the 3v3 ranked games.Another thing (which is not a real problem now, but seems it will be when the game meta starts settling in) is the lack of a pick and ban system for matches. Queuing as your favourite champ is fun but in ranked matches I think that picks and counter picks will start to play a major role in hte future, otherwise it's just luck being paired with an enemy character you counter (or vice-versa). Maybe a traditional pick and ban system is not suitable for this game and they will probably have to come up with something. In the meantime the meta isn't yet established and there is no need for it, it's everybody's game and experimenting is the norm.[ GRAPHICS ]I didn't really like Wow and Torchlight's art style that much, but I think Stunlock Studio pulled it off very well.I really like the character design, color palette, animations and textures, nothing stands outs too much but in a good way. For me the aestethics of the game are well executed and they suit with the overall spirit of the game.The interface is not confusing but I don't really have any major praise for it, it just works. The one complain I have is that there is too much space from your character to your abilities at the bottom of your screen, therefore looking at your cooldowns is often a problem. I would like for this reason to have maybe little icons ontop or under your character to show which abilities are recharging.-- CONCLUSIONS --In my opinion Battlerite is a really good game for a specific audience of competitive players and hits the spot in almost every aspect. I will have to see if it will keep being fun even after hundreds of hours like other major competitive games, but for what I have seen so far it has all the cards to do so.8.5 / 10"
