76561198040713751,Recommended,504370,31091121,Posted: 11 April,all,nemanja472,"The game features 10 minute matches of intense competitive gameplay. No farming, no items, no randomness, no death timers, no picks and bans, only pure condensed mechanical skill and mind-games. For anyone that enjoyed the WoW arena format and wants a more engaging combat system, this is the go-to game.There are 20 champions in the game currently, with each having a unique playstyle. Battlerites, which are the perks that you choose before each round, are a bit lacking, but the Devs have managed to make quite a few characters have more than one viable build.The playerbase is small, although that is visible only in the ranks of Diamond/Champion/Grand Champion.That is all not too surprising because the game is in early access and behind a paywall. The price is well worth it, especially on sale,  because it includes all current and future champions. This is crucial for people who like to play on and off without the burden of being left behind with locked content.Cosmetics are still not that diverse, but that is not to say that they aren't working on that too. They just did a graphical update for a champion as well as a gorgeous legendary skin.The recent addition of Bakko Brawl confirms that they are exploring new fun game modes which is always nice. This particular one promotes the use of cast cancel, an integral game mechanic for higher levels of play.The community has its gatherings on Reddit and Discord and so do some of the Devs. They answer questions, take feedback, post Devblogs weekly and even stream sometimes. All in all, a pretty cool environment.It feels like they really want to present a more polished product before full release and, in my opinion, they're getting closer slowly, but steadily.Definitely give it a go in the free week!"
