,Recommended,504370,33323446,Posted: 6 July,all,lenkek,"Very unique, competitive, and fun game. WASD movement, skills are really skillshots, and fast rounds.It's an Arena Brawler, not like LoL, DotA, and HotS where it has 3 lanes that has creeps and towers. It's like a colosseum, no towers or creeps, an open area with thats is pretty suitable for this type of gameplay with skillshots, WASD movement, and fast rounds.For casuals, this game is great, you have daily and weekly quests, and alongside to new players, there's achievements that they can unlock. All of these daily quests, weekly quests, and achievements, you will gain rewards such as cosmetic chests and ingame currency.Everyone has an equal playing field, no runes or masteries that give you a head start in the game, also no buying items. Instead, at the beginning of each round everybody has an option to chose 1 out of the 3 ""battlerites"" given to them for their character which allow you to customize your abilities and playstyle.Combat is really fluid, thanks to WASD and skillshots, every character's kit seems to fit well with the gamestyle. The game is easy to grasp, but hard and rewarding to master.Every champion is viable, just certain team compositions are not good against other compositions. This game's balance is okay, no character is broken since every character can be countered. Characters are more balanced in 3v3s than in 2v2s, since you have more variety of champions to play with and against. If you're looking for the most balanced game mode, it's going to be 3v3s, but not much people play 3v3s.Battlerite's playerbase is okay, nothing you need to worry about, there's 2.5k people playing each day, its not going to decline, it's in Early Access, its completely fine.Nothing wrong with ranked matchmaking during this stage of the game. Only 2.5k players playing the game each day during peak times, you can expect going against the same people a couple times. Yes you will be matched with others higher than you, but if you dont win against them, then you dont deserve to get up to that rank, so don't complain. If you dont want to go against people higher than you, you use ""Strict Matchmaking"" which sets you to play with others are your rank, but you'll have to compensate for the time to search for players at your rank.For only $20, for all the champions (including all the future ones), and for 400+ hours I have on it, this game is worth the money. More features are to come, watching this game develop since October, 2016, its a very promising game. I have fun each day playing it."
