,Not Recommended,504370,31272062,Posted: 21 April,all,punished,"TL;DR - Although playable, I can't recommend it in it's current state.Okay gameplay, nice graphics, well optimized enough that it can run on low end computers, customizations (although limited) are goodBad matchmaking, bad ranking system, bad community, unoptimized/bad mechanics, noticeable balance problems, more luck based than skill based, player base is dying.LONG READ:I regret paying for this game after seeing what it looks like in it's current state.As simple and fun as the gameplay might be, most of the mechanicss are still as broken as my hand after hitting the desk in anger and frustration because of the♥♥♥♥♥♥happening in it.Ranking system is a complete mess; you're not ranking up based on how well you play or how many points you made in the entire match, no, ranking is basically win based. You get an empty bar, you win a match, bar fills with a tiny orange-red chunk of predetermined static value that is always the same for every win; what happens if you lose a match, same thing but in reverse, you have your bar sucked back down to where you started from.Games are more luck based than skill based and the matchmaking is just bad. You can easily get matched with a bad team and no matter how well you play, you'll end up violated because your team either has badly matched champions or the enemy team has a pair of champions that are next to impossible to beat when they're put together. Then there are also those who lose on purpouse to get deranked so they can troll lower ranked players.Ranking is frustrating as you waste an entire day playing, growing in rank, then the next day it's all back to where you started from because you're matched up with bad teams, derankers or ragequitters; leaving you with no choice but to either continue playing and lose or just forfeit the match; either way it's a rank loss.Balance problems are visible as well; one of them being the fact that you can match up 2 champions in the same team which are next to impossible to beat together, or champions who have easily abusable invincibility frames and you can close to spam their abilities which get you a few frames of invincibility during castingThe community isn't exactly the best either as most are going to write in chat ''easy xD'' ''gg'' ''git gud'' ''ez'' whenever they win a round or the entire match but when they lose, they're going to swear and insult you; also there are quite a bunch of ragequitters who leave the match after they're killed once.Unless you enjoy being constantly angry and frustrated, don't buy the game. Best you can do is just wait it out until the early access is over and the game gets released as a F2P title or play it when it get a free weekend pass."
