76561198038672694,Recommended,504370,25630694,"Posted: 21 September, 2016",all,Kalrik,"I'm blown away by this game. I've put in a few hours and already ran in to a few really competent players, and the combat feels so polished and deep. Listen to what people are saying. It's great.Turn DOTA2 or LoL into a top down shooter and remove all the MOBA junk. No need to worry about farming or item builds or any strange mastery/rune/whatever system outside of the game. It's fast paced arena combat.As someone looking for an alternative to Overwatch because I haven't been enjoying shooters lately and DOTA2/LoL because I don't have the time for long games, this really scratched my itch. Matches are 10-15 minutes depending on how close the fights are. It's freeing to not have to sit down and dedicate an hour to what might end up being a totally unenjoyable stomp.At this point, after a few hours, the heroes feel balanced. They each have a very similar set of skills in function but in practice they play very differently. It makes it easier to pick up and learn a new hero but it's definitely going to take time to really master.If you're looking for a fast paced game that's accessible but incredibly deep in terms of mechanics and micro, pick this up. I can't wait to see what new content they put out in the near future. Get in on the ground floor of this one, because I can see people getting extremely good extremely fast."
