76561198049510566,Recommended,504370,33777490,Posted: 24 July,all,WHAT IN TARNATION,"This game is amazing. Play it. Imagine a MOBA, but without the tedious gold/experience farming and the item-based systems that lend themselves to snowballing. Imagine a MOBA where every autoattack required aim to hit with, an entirely skill-based MOBA where, even if down to rounds to one, you can still come back by changing your own strategy and gameplay. Battlerite, the spiritual successor to Bloodline Champions, is easily the best MOBA I've ever played, indeed it is the only redeeming title in a largely stagnant genre. Great yet simple gameplay, action that gets your heart pounding, and the best thing is that even if losing badly, three rounds only take a maximum of 6 minutes. Short and sweet, and for those of us who already grind for money 8 hours a day, it represents a needed and welcome change to the MOBA genre, filled with titles where you farm for a minimum of 20 minutes before the teamfights actually start. This is the MOBA genre's saving grace."
,Not Recommended,504370,31145584,Posted: 14 April,all,PhoenixRhapsody,"The core mechanics in the game are solid, it's engaging to play, but the balance of the heroes is hilariously imbalanced. There are still 3 OP characters that win 90% of the time in a skilled player's hands.The way the game is set up there are a few major things to consider per character to decide their strength. First is damage output. A lot of characters, like Ashka, Jade, and Iva all have absurd burst. They can also kite. They are strong for those reasons alone, but then you add in decent projectile speeds, high AoE, or CC and you have a very strong character.Secondly is healing. Burst healing is infinitely better than delayed healing, meaning that unless you're dealing with someone that can't aim or outmaneuver you, your slow heals aren't going to give you much chance. Certain healers have massive healing potential, like Poloma, and she can even prevent damage, but it is fast and strong healing. She's absurdly overpowered for that reason.Lastly is attack speed. A few of the characters do not attack fast. Among these there are some that also have weak attack. While that isn't always a limiter, in the cases of slow attacks and weak ones, there needs to be some over-coming factor. Ashka attacks slow, but he hits hard. Croak attacks fast, but has weaker attacks and toxin DoT. Something that separates them from Varesh is that he only gets effective usefulness if he can successfully combo his abilities, relying on heavy synergy to be effective. This stacks against him with his slow attacks speed, which makes him woefully weak overall.Without a more effective look at balancing the characters to provide either burst or sustained DPS/utility, most of the characters in this game are not going to be competitive or even casually playable."
