,Recommended,504370,30045599,Posted: 19 February,all,My Sweet Banana,"Way back in the day, I downloaded Bloodline Champions and thought it was awesome.  A week later I tried to log in and there was no one on.I jumped over to DoTA2, but the matches were entirely too long and not quite what I was looking for as far as combat.From there I played League of Legends, though a bit more fast-paced and containing other game modes for more intimate matches - nothing came close to those couple dozen hours I played on Bloodline Champions.In mumble one day, I describe Bloodline Champions and someone tells me about its successor, Battlerite.Holy♥♥♥♥♥♥ thank god this game exists.  I don't have the fortitude to sit through long MOBA matches and the high-octane pace of this game suits me perfectly.  I may not have the fortitude for MOBA matches, but I can bang out games in Battlerite for -hours-.The differences between 2v2 and 3v3 matches are vast enough that changing between can refresh your experience for a few hours a clip.Although I am glad I paid for this game, I truly hope it goes free so we can get more folks playing.  This game is competetive enough to stand beside other free-to-play competetive games.The only feedback I have regarding this game is the presentation, which I see they are vigorously working on.Since this is arena-style gameplay, I feel the game can be presented with a little more punch.  When I lock into a queue with my desired hero, why not a little voice clip announcing their name?  The same goes for round transitions, why not announce it like a fighting game?A lot of Smash Clones take this from the Smash Bros. formula, but I feel it's an integral part of getting you interested in the characters.  Constantly reinforcing the character's names helps new players learn the names of your cast, and reminds the forgetful players.  Their names are also missing from the scoreboards as well.  As these are new characters to all of us, having their name present or accessible at all times is important to that reinforcement.I'd also like character-specific bindings if possible.Aside from my lengthy nitpick, this game is absolutely wonderful and fills in a huge disparity  between MOBA's and Fighters.  It can act as a bridge, or a middle ground.  This game feels balanced well, new heroes are steadily coming in - the designs are great and devs seem to have their ear to the players.10/10.5"
