76561197970466934,Recommended,504370,25621542,"Posted: 21 September, 2016",all,Connatic,"This game is Bloodline Champions reborn. A ""reboot"" if you will. If you are familiar with BLC, you will see the core gameplay is the same. The game play is slowed down a tad, perspective changed slightly from BLC, but overall makes it feel like a better game and more accessable. I was only a casual BLC player, but I can already tell playing Battlerite was much easier to get into.To summerize the gameplay, it feels like the core meta game of Arena inWorld of Warcraft, with action twin-stick shooter mechanics. Everything is a skill shot and there are many cooldowns to manage. With counters, shields, teleports, CC, etc.  It makes the game very skill based with lots of room to grow and improve just by landing the shots alone, nevermind cooldown management and timings.One major feature changed from BLC was the new ""Battlerite"" system. Each match is a best of 5. At the begining of each round you choose a ""Battlerite"". Which is essentially a talent that will buff or add effects to your abilities. Much like leveling up in ""Heroes of the Storm."" It adds a little sense of progression and just ramps up the action.You play these matches in a 2v2 or 3v3 format. Overall it becomes a very satisfying experience. One round you can get totally destroyed, and turn it all around the next by playing better and smarter. There is great satisfaction to taking a round away from an opposing team who was obviously dominating the first two.While some BLC fanatics might be off put by some of the changes they made, I feel the overall experience is better for players new to this style of game, and BLC fans will just be happy to have it back in some form or another.Currently it is in Early Access, but definitely feels like a complete game. Just missing some of the social features and game modes from their orignal game, Bloodline Champions. Early Access will pretty much be mostly for getting these missing features ready, more champions to add, and of course balance feedback. It will launch with what we are assuming a traditional F2P model, with free champion rotations that you have to unlock with money or ingame currency.  Buying into Early Access now essentially gives you a MASSIVE pre-order bonus. All Champions free, forever! Pretty sweet deal for having faith in Stunlock studios. I reccomend this game for anyone who is a fan for high skill based competative mulitplayer games."
