76561198048348178,Recommended,504370,25689867,"Posted: 25 September, 2016",all,Uncle Grim,"Game is still in early access, as I was playing I experienced a great deal of rubber banding from the server (it occured during the tutorial and vs AI).I'm not going to hold it against the game at this point as that's the purpose of an Alpha/Beta build, to fix those issues.The game also uses a dual currency similar to other F2P games. If you pay for this game at this stage you get the entire ~12ish roster of champions (might be a few more or less), and you get to just have fun playing.I wouldn't be surprised if this game ended up free to play, personally I'm not a fan of Micro Transactions inside a game I paid to play, cosmetic or not if I'm paying for a product I'm buying the content not a portion of it. Fights are intense, matches last about 10 minutes depending on how even the sides are, 1 round takes at worst 2.5 minutes, if at worse case you play 5 rounds (first to 3 wins) thats 2.5*5 = 12.5 minutes.TL;DR:Pros:Good game, fun, very skill based,Matches are Short but intense (Avg 7-12minutes)Game ""feels"" balanced (Your character could be statistically under-powered but you can easily outplay your opponent)Art is pretty (Almost Torchlight-esque)Cons:Network issues (Early Access)MicroTransactions in a game you purchased (It's cosmetic currently as you can only buy chests, similar to OverWatch, but it could apply to other content down the pipeline)Fun game, would recommend to people if they're on the fence, but I'll pass on it until it goes Free to Play, or they've stabilized their servers more (rubber banding in a PvP game is no bueno)."
