,Recommended,504370,31697546,Posted: 12 May,all,Colo,"Very exciting team-based gameplay. Major emphasis on action/reaction. It's a good brawler, with lots of outplay potential, a very high skill ceiling, and a moderate skill floor. I have a lot of fun with it. There are a multitude of playstyles that are enhanced through Battlerites, and the development team have been actively balancing and rebalancing as required. There are ranked and unranked modes, and the developers have been toying with secondary game modes, such as the Easter event of Bakko's Egg Brawl.Battlerites are modifications to your abilities, three choices presented per round; these can be as simple as making an ability do a little more damage, or adding a new mechanic to one of your existing skills, or introducing a debuff to another ability. Some Battlerites are a bit underwhelming on their respective tiers, but are overall well balanced to allow the player to make dynamic choices on a round-by-round basis. Sometimes you need control, sometimes you need utility, and sometimes you can do it with a bit more damage.As the game is in Early Access, the balance sometimes shifts in directions that I don't personally agree with, but overall, it's a fun, competitive game. You can most certainly play it alone or with friends, and I enjoy playing it fairly casually (in the Casual queue).It is a MOBA in the truest sense; Multiplayer Online Battle Arena. It's not a Dotalike."
