,Not Recommended,504370,35141718,Posted: 22 September,all,Cleril,"The game is not fun.If you win you will be satisfied you didn't encounter a flavor of the month champion.  You'll love having a competent, non-berating teammate.  You'll be bored because your enemies just weren't good enough for you.  You'll question hitboxes.If you lose you'll blame the flavor of the month champion.  You'll hate having an incompetent, berating teammate.  You'll be bored and frustrated wondering why you aren't playing something fun.The gameplay is not fun.  If the fun you can have with a game is determined by those two statements above (and it is) you cannot have fun.  Its simply not possible.  Sure you might get a rush out of killing your opponent out of a tough 1v1.  More often than not you're wondering why X skill's hitbox is so big or how Y skill has zero windup to react to it.Characters play different only insofar that their pacing is different.  Ashka for example is slow but hard hitting with ranged attacks.  Ezmo is quick but soft hitting with ranged attacks.  There's very little differentiation between the characters compared to Bloodline Champions.  Try to think of some defining feature of each character and you really can't.  Sure you can point to a skill that nobody has (like Ezmo's straight line heal) but it exists in other paced forms.  Ashka can heal as well but again more slowly and bursty.There's no satisfactory variety.  There's no fun that isn't determined by everything you can't influence.  The gameplay itself is not actually fun regardless of that.  You move and shoot out similar abilities against humans who do similar things ad nausem.  Its the same tedium as all other MOBAs with the fat trimmed out but the meat is rotten because MOBAs inherently are not fun.That's why these games have grinding systems in place.  Skinner boxes are ""fun"" for humans.  But would they really be necessary if the game itself was fun.  Probably not."
