76561198051462553,Not Recommended,504370,27017736,"Posted: 23 November, 2016",all,Suplax,"----- Update 26/12/2016 ------I can't still recommend the game because of a single reason , Devs shameless micro transaction practice.The ranking system DID improve on the last patch , yet the matchmaking is still chaos , now we have proper ranks but for some reason the matchmaking put Bronze/Silver people competing with/against Diamond players for some reason.Anyway the main reason I can't recommend the game right now it's the micro transaction robbery that devs don't even comment about it.The way you get skin/mounts/weapons in this game is by opening chests that you buy either with gold or real money ,you can directly obtain SOME skins/weapons/mounts with Crystals.Gold is ONLY warded by winning matches , you need to win a lot of then though.Crystals are awarded when you get a DUPLICATED of an item you already have after opening chests.The problem here is:  Event chests are overpriced and items from event chest are ONLY awarded by actually opening the chests.Items from Event chests CANNOT be bought with Crystals , and the Duplicate RATE is ridiculous.It costs A LOT of gold so people are actually forced to buy the chests with real money instead of trying to play for it.Not to mention the price in real money is cheap in some countries and extremely overpriced in others.In summary:  You buy Event chests with real money (because it's overpriced with gold) end up with A LOT of duplicates who are transformed in crystals that you CAN'T use to buy the event items. Simply a shameless and absurd practice by the devs.======================================================================I really wish I could give a neutral Review score , but since I can't , I'll go with negative until the game is improved.It's a really fun game , it really takes the pressure If you been playing MOBA like me for years , it may look like MOBA , but it's just really a Deathmatch game between heroes , simple as that.The game is a really good though , pure skill based , you fight in matches 2x2 or 3x3 , the matches fast paced and it won't take too much of your time , yet it make your heart pump fast.The controls are really good and the graphics are nice as well.The community is not very toxic , YET , but you always find people taking gaming too serious...But we have to remember it's a Early Access game, and that is where the problem lies , I normally don't buy EA games , but I was in need of a good game after abandoning League of Legends after playing it for years.Battlerite fit the ""empty space"" , but with some flaws...First , there aren't enough Heroes to keep you interested for countless hours. ( yet , hopefully )After spending more than 120 hours I got to say I'm a bit tired of the same heroes.Second and the biggest failure in my opinion is the matchmaking.Matchmaking it's buggy and unbalanced at the moment.Ranking is divided by Grades , being Grade 15 the top , where only the best players are at.The ranked battles ( where most people are ) function as the same as any ranked game  , you win a match you get points ,you lost a match you lose points , and if you get enough points you climb a Grade.Currently I'm at Grade 12 and it's getting really impossible to climb right now , because for some reason IF there isn't enough players of your grade online the system put you against or with players of grades below / above , but here is the catch:IF you get into a match against players of LOWER grade , even if you win , you end up losing points. ( like it's my fault)So the game end up punishing you because the lack of players / bad matchmaking system.IF you get into a match against players of grades ABOVE yours and you lose ( because obviously they are better than you , so odds are against you ) you also lose points.So in essence , you got to hope that the matchmaking put you with teammates of the SAME grade against people of the SAME grade , or you're done.And third , the report system is a joke.It doesn't happen often , but I've already seem people being racist , people raging and insulting and rage quit as well.I've reported people like that , sometimes the same toxic person , and nothing is done.I believe the punishment should be faster and more severe , so the game community does not turn into another LoL , but I guess the devs are really not worried since the money is coming.As for now I'll stop playing the game for a while until some updates are done , probably going to move on to another game.The value is not bad  , since I've more than 120 hours I believe my money was worth it , and taking into account that if one day I return all heroes will be unlocked. ( ASSUMING the game does not die )But I would recommend waiting for a sale discount to get this one."
