,Not Recommended,504370,25888895,"Posted: 6 October, 2016",all,CryonicSuspension,"A fun game that started to get boring around the 40 hour mark. The cracks in the game started to show:Pros:- High skill ceiling.- Nice  music.- The game features the ability to create private games where you can fight AI. You can tailor the intelligence level of each character on the team, which is a cool feature.Miscellaneous:- Essentially a MOBA without the tedium / complexity of towers, minions and farming. An arena game similar, yet not as good as ""Forge"".Cons:- Unbalanced characters. Current tier list ( I don't agree with some of the placments but you can get a rough feel for the game here ):https://www.tentonhammer.com/articles/battlerite-tier-listUnbalanced characters eventually made it boring to play the mandated, handful of overpowered characters, in the very limited 15 character roster.- Heavy handed nerfs from the developers. Poloma was an overpowered support character that had her range nerfed, turning her into gank-bait by ranged DPS. I think that she mostly spends her time running from one side of the map to the other now. The obvious balance change would have been to simply reduce her DPS, 1 point at a time, to each skill and see how it played out. That would have been an example of intelligent micro-management.- The match-making system is god awful. You could be paired up with someone who just installed the game 15 minutes ago. 3v3 often devolves into, ""Whichever team has the new player, loses"". The queue times are very fast but at the expense of balanced teams. I'm predicting that between now and the game going Free-to-Play in Q1 2017, the player base will drop even further ( it went from 13,160 to 8,220 within two weeks ):http://steamcharts.com/app/504370#All- The match-making system uses the Trueskill system, so if you are familiar with the game SMITE and the daily complaints and inevitable threadlocks, regarding match-making, you will be familiar with Battlerite:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TrueSkillhttp://forums.smitegame.com/forumdisplay.php?167-General-SMITE-DiscussionRealistically, there's no way to analyze a battle and assign a numeral that represents how well someone did, you'd need a next-generation IBM Watson with Deep Learning / Google AlphaGo  supercomputer to do that. One thing that games can stop doing is putting new players with ranked players ( new players should be paired with new players and go from there ). Queue times would be longer but the question is, would you rather wait a few minutes, to get an evenly matched game, or have a fast, yet meaningless landslide in either direction ( which I consider a terrific waste of time ).- The rewards system consists of giving a handful of points for a win but heavily penalizing a loss. Eventually, I noticed that I had spent an entire day losing the minimal gains that I had eeked out. Since every game is a ranked game, you are basically screwed in solo queue and the only way to play the game is with a pre-made. The rewards system gets funny when you are awarded +1 or +0 for a win, especially if you overcame higher ranked oponents. The only way to receive the maximum reward is to win 3-0 and even then, there's no guarentee that you will receive a decent reward. The game fails to recognize miraculous comebacks. In one game we ended up winning 3-2 with me being a grade 8 Croak ( assassin ) and solo killing a Grade 9 Croak and a Grade 10 Sirius ( Healer-DPS ) in a ""last man standing scenario"". My team consisted of Grade 7's, so they got destroyed quickly. My reward: +1 point. It's a slap in the face. It gets even worse though - someone randomly disconnects or AFKs on your team and you receive -20 or -30 points.This is a review for the Early Access version of the game that currently costs $21.99 Canadian dollars. Between now and the game being officially released in Q1 2017, the game will be patched multiple times, have new characters added and become Free-to-Play, at which point this review will become obsolete.Although I don't think that this game is worth $20, there's never any reason not to take a look at a Free-to-Play game. I'm predicting that toxicity in the game will go through the roof when it goes Free-to-Play though..."
