,Recommended,504370,30405496,Posted: 9 March,all,strato,"Battlerite has been called by many a moba, and while I certainly understand how it could be identified as such, I shall proceed to reject any such notion. For many gamers, the word moba brings to mind league of legends, or dota 2. It creates a vision of one sitting in a lane against an enemy, last hitting creeps, accumulating gold, and in general, a long and monotonous experience. Battlerite, on the other hand, flings players face first into the action. It's like that girl you asked out who tells you she wants to focus on school, in contrast with the girl who tells you no because you're ugly as hell. Battlerite delivers pure, eccentric, and strategic combat. It gets to the damn point with none of that last hitting ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥t for 20 minutes followed by walking around until some idiot gets caught out. Battlerite, at it's essence, is a tavern brawl you find yourself embroiled in minutes after grabbing a drink, whilst moba's are a pointless war you (probably will) end up in because some idiot decided to run for president. With experienced devs, a mostly welcome community, and amazing core gameplay, I simply have nothing but praise for this game."
