,Recommended,504370,30111940,Posted: 22 February,all,nEmo,"TLDR: Game is incredibly fast paced and well polished. Has easily become one of my favourite games on the market. Low player base is unsettling however it is still early access and will go F2P in quarter 1 of 2017 so it should pick up shortly. If you have the cash it's worth the buy however at the time of this review F2P isnt far off so it may be worth the wait.This game has it's ups and downs with me but I still find myself having a good time playing it from time to time. My first experience with this game was a little upsetting as I thought the game wasnt balanced very well until I later realized that I was simply trash and that the tutorial skips out on some key aspects of gameplay. If you are a new player venturing into this game I would definitely recommend looking up some guides to further understand how the dynamics of this game work and patch the knowledge gaps the tutorial leaves you with.Personally I recommend using this youtube video I found that is both informative and genuinly enjoyable to watch as well.{https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bP1Az5kpS98}After learning some of the key elements to the game from outside sources you will notice that this information has allowed you to identify where and when you should be a little bit better. It's also around this time that you begin to realize that there is a fairly large learning curve associated with this game. I myself struggled with this moment and I found that playing with others [Friends, helpful individuals]  who are able to give constructive feedback not only helps improve your game but provides that morale boost to keep on grinding. Eventually you will come to a point where you are no longer enjoying the ease of the ""Casual"" mode and you will move into the competitive scene where the difficulty ratchets and your ego deflates. The matches at this point become incredibly intense and in my mind this is where the heart of the game is. The competitive though a little wonky in its initial placement rankings is so mind bogglingly fun. It has been a good while since I have had a game bring my heart rate to a blazing fast speed but I genuinely feel this when I get down to the end of a match.Though I could likely rant about my personal experience and enjoyment in this game for months I am going to bring it on down to a pro's and con's list.Pro:-Fast Paced Combat-Quick Matches-Decent Hero Selection-Attentive Developers-Visually Appealing-Intense Competitive Format-Interesting Game MechanicsCon:-Uninformative Tutorial-Steep Learning Curve [Not too much of a con here, however some people may see it that way]-Early Access Small Player Base-Pre-Match Hero Selection [Again not too huge of an issue here especially if you are with a group who can build from lobby but this game does not matchmake according to selected roles... It just throws people together]"
