76561197976763267,Recommended,504370,25763181,"Posted: 29 September, 2016",all,Downloaded,"As someone who has spent thousands of hours in League of Legends but no longer has the time required to commit to a game like that, Battlerite is a really great experience that nails the tactics of team fighting while trimming the other bits like farming and lane management (which are great in themselves but aren't missed in this package that feels like a complete experience on its own).  This game makes you feel like you're in control of a cool action sequence from a high budget fantasy film every 10 minutes, and the wide array of characters means your matches will contain a significant amount of variety.My only criticism is that of the planned free to play model.  I can understand the appeal of f2p - I played League for years and did not mind the unlock grind, but having moved to Overwatch in recent months I have come to really respect allowing players to have all of the characters for free while providing fun cosmetics to unlock and/or buy for cash.  It feels good to buy a game and know you have everything available from the get go, and I wish Battlerite would consider a similar model instead.  I would even be willing to pay for expansion packs or something, because it shows that developers respect my time and money enough to let me focus on playing the full game without suffering from grinding for new characters and dealing with the flood of free champions every week that became tedious in League of Legends after a while.  If they do a good job supporting the game with cool content updates, skins, mounts, voicelines, etc I am sure people will throw a few bucks their way to support the developers and access the fun cosmetics."
