76561198050263083,Recommended,504370,25703957,"Posted: 25 September, 2016",all,THE PWNER,"This game is a fast paced bullet/slashing hell. In Battlerite you play as a champion (either a melee, support, or ranged champion) and either do 2v2 or 3v3 against AI or other players. There is a ranking system that palces you against other players of equal level as you which allows players to compete against other players with equal skill. Champions can be leveled up and as a result the player may recieve coin, gems, or chests (coins and gems are used to edit the champion while chests give random outfits and such). The chamion ranking stops at level 10 and sorta forces you to take on a new champion which is a bit of a bummer. Now the gameplay itself is fun, fast, and overall well made. You will find yourself in close situations where it is only you and one other players as the arena shrinks around the two of you. Then you either clutch it and rain victorious or get rekt and begin to cry a little bit. The game has little bugs, yet needs some improvments such as more champions, more new diverse maps, and finally a larger level up range for champions (maybe a small bonus or special outfit/weapon to show off). Overall, I reccomend the game to anyone who wants a fast paced exciting game. I give Battlerite 9/10 Croaks"
