76561198027913056,Recommended,504370,25690009,"Posted: 25 September, 2016",all,Arqan,"As many of you know, Battlerite is a ""glorified"" remake of Bloodline Champions. And boy,  is it a much better game now.+ An interesting roster of characters, most of which have a nice skill ceiling and can ""make plays"" when used correctly+ (fairly) Easy to learn, hard to master+ Short, dynamic games (usually up to 10 minutes for the entire match)+ Responsive controls backed by good servers (much unlike BLC)+ Visually pleasing with (imo) way better art style than BLC+ Attention to details (small talk between characters as the match starts, short bullet time when someone goes down etc.)- Only one game mode - 2v2 or 3v3 TDM (I know game's an arena pvp but a 5v5 conquest mode on larger maps could be a lot of fun)- Some balance issues (to be expected at this stage really)- Game lacks some sense of progression (there is ELO, ranks and hero levels but it feels lacking to me)Overall the cons are pretty minor (and the last two are most likely going to be fixed by the time Battlerite releases as f2p title) and I'd give this game a solid 8.5/10. Pretty damn good for an early access title!"
