,Recommended,504370,25704846,"Posted: 25 September, 2016",all,Stick Mick,"TLDR:If you like the team fights of MOBAs, or WoW arenas - but don't like the grinding to get there: You will probably like this game.~~~~~~~~~~2v2/3v3 team-based twin-stick skill-shot fantasy-themed arena combat.Payment Model:Currently all characters are unlocked, and there is no equipment, levels, or other boosting methods.A fresh account has the exact same combat ability of a verteran.Purchases bring cosmetic items, and there is a founders DLC that gives +10% xp to you and your party - but levels only reward cosmetics anyway.The game is going free to play, and if they stick with this shop model - they're off to a good start.Gameplay:Combat is fast paced, 100% skillshot.Players are placed at opposite ends of a mirror arena, best of 5 rounds wins.Between rounds, each player is offered an upgrade - that puts a different spin on an existing skill.These modifications are chosen from a predetermined pool per character per round - increasing in power as the rounds go on.These can offer more uses, extra effects, more damage, etc. This allows players to customise their character to their playstyle - with an extra skill in choosing modifications that counter your opponents.There's more active abilities than the average MOBA, with each character having at least 7 skills. Some are on cooldown, some consume charge generated by using other abilities.Beware if your internet isn't great, or you live in a remote area - since even small amounts of latency will cost you matches. (Rejoice Australians, there are AUS servers!)Progression:Since combat is skill-based, there's a high skill ceiling to each character, with use of skills and positioning being crucial to success.In early access, no characters are unlocked over time, but cosmetic items are earned by leveling characters and completing daily missions (to use characters from certain pools).There's no gear treadmill to grind here.Story:Nearly non-existant, giving only short backstories on characters, no single player campaign.Graphics:A high fantasy art style, combat animations are clear in purpose.The top down shooter view means you rarely get a close look at the models, but they are good enough.Sound:Music is enough to get the point across without being distracting, and the sound design doesn't have any jarring misses."
